    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1977-10-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1977-10-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="173"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d173">
                <head>173. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_BZ_1">Brzezinski</persName>) to Secretary of Defense
                        <persName corresp="#p_BH_2">Brown</persName> and Secretary of Energy
                        <persName corresp="#p_SJR_1">Schlesinger</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d173fn1">Source: Washington National Records
                        Center, <gloss target="#t_OSD_1">OSD</gloss> Files: <gloss target="#t_FRC_1"
                            >FRC</gloss> 330–80–0017, Box 63, A–400.112 1977. Secret. Copies sent to
                            <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_BH_2">Harold Brown</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_LTB_1"
                            >Lance</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BGS_1">George Brown</persName>,
                        and <persName corresp="#p_TSM_1">Turner</persName>. <persName
                            corresp="#p_BH_2">Harold Brown</persName> wrote in the upper right-hand
                        corner of the memorandum, “10/22 <gloss target="#t_HB_1">HB</gloss>.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1977-10-20">October 20, 1977</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_FY_1">FY</gloss> 1978 Underground Nuclear Test Program
                        (CRESSET)</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has approved the underground nuclear test program for the first
                    half of <gloss target="#t_FY_1">FY</gloss> 1978 (CRESSET I), consistent with the
                        <gloss target="#t_FY_1">FY</gloss> 1978 <gloss target="#t_DOD_1">DOD</gloss>
                    and DOE budget levels, and subject to the following limitations:</p>
                <p>—Approval of the BACKSTAY and KNIGHTHEAD tests is held in abeyance pending <gloss
                        target="#t_DOD_1">DOD</gloss> submission and interagency review of a study
                    of the military utility and arms control implications of insertable nuclear
                    components.</p>
                <p>—Implementation must be in accordance with existing policy regarding testing near
                    the 150 kt limit of the <gloss target="#t_TTBT_1">TTBT</gloss>.</p>
                <p>The above approval is conditional upon the outcome of the <gloss
                        target="#t_CTB_1">CTB</gloss> negotiations; the United States must be
                    prepared to cease testing if agreement on a <gloss target="#t_CTB_1">CTB</gloss>
                    Treaty is reached.</p>
                <p>Specific approval of the test program for the second half of <gloss
                        target="#t_FY_1">FY</gloss> 1978 (CRESSET II) should be requested by March
                    1978. The total number of tests to be conducted during <gloss target="#t_FY_1"
                        >FY</gloss> 1978 is not to exceed 25.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BZ_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Zbigniew Brzezinski</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
